Fix app.pro qmake call. The problem is that the command is executed from the 

  build-amd64/app/obj

directory instead of build-amd64/app.

Full build command:

cd app/ && make -f Makefile all
/usr/local/bin/qmake4 DESKTOPDIR=/usr/local/share/applications ICONDIR=/usr/local/share/pixmaps MIMEDIR=/usr/local/share/mime/packages LRELEASECOMMAND=lrelease4 PREFIX=/usr/local QMAKE_CFLAGS=-O2\ -pipe\ \  QMAKE_CFLAGS_RELEASE=-O2\ -pipe\ \  QMAKE_CXX=c++ QMAKE_CXXFLAGS=-O2\ -pipe\ \  QMAKE_CXXFLAGS_RELEASE=-O2\ -pipe\ \  QMAKE_LFLAGS= QMAKE_LFLAGS_RELEASE= -o Makefile ../../app/app.pro
Cannot find file: ../../app/app.pro.

